
### $Id$ ###

To install pyxser, extract the tarball content, then:

python ./setup.py --verbose clean --all
python ./setup.py --verbose build --force
python ./setup.py --verbose install

To build a debug install:

python ./setup.py --verbose clean --all
env CFLAGS='-Wall -Wextra -Wshadow -pedantic -std=c99' python ./setup.py --verbose build --force --debug
python ./setup.py --verbose install

Thanks for using and testing... enjoy pyxser ;)

Ubuntu/Kubuntu/Xubuntu Users:
pyxser needs the following packages for building: libxml2, libxml2-dbg,
libxml2-dev, libxml2-doc, libxml2-utils, python-libxml2, python-libxml2-dbg,
python, python-dev

I think that Debian needs similar packages... plese be carefull on building
this module, read some manuals on installing non distribution-standard
Python modules.

